{
  "texts": [
    "Afterward, edge convolution followed by a pooling operation p is applied on each N(i) to learn embedded features.",
    "The edge convolution is given by Eqs. 1-3 [18].",
    "Here Eq. 1 encodes global information as x g i, Eq.",
    "2 encodes local neighborhood information as x l i and Eq. 3 combines both global information and local neighborhood information as x c i. h is implemented as a shared MLP.The choice of pooling operation p is an important aspect to consider [25].",
    "The pioneering work of PointNet [14] and DGCNN [18] established max-pooling as a widely adopted choice within this domain."
  ]
}